"viable" means they can be used in a match without being at a disadvantage just for being that champion. An example of a non-viable champion would be like {{champion:429}} who is intentionally weaker and terrible because she is so oppressive when given even a slight amount of power.  

Their builds don't matter because their primary goal is to deal damage or they deal a lot of damage regardless of their build, even if they build full tank. They are all melee, whether they have ranged abilities or not is irrelevant.
